1968;;A Place for Lovers;;American;;Vittorio De Sica;;Faye Dunaway, Marcello Mastroianni;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Place_for_Lovers;;The rich fashion designer Julia is tired of living because she knows she is suffering from a malignant cancer. When the woman leaves for her last holiday in Cortina d'Ampezzo, she meets the young and vital Valerio. The two fall in love instantly, but Julia does not reveal her secret to Valerio. When Valerio finds out that she is sick and dying, he decides to pretend to know nothing, continuing his love affair with Julia to the end.